      "role": "user",
      "content": "okay, i see what you mean about the wording. but you're still kind of dancing around the point. if we're talking about a \"human right,\" doesn't that make the argument for \"economic efficiency\" or \"market competition\" irrelevant? like, if something is a fundamental right, isn't it settled that the government has to provide it, no matter what the cost or the bureaucracy looks like?",
